    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i've been trying that but i keep seeing these little tiny gaps or cracks showing up in the mud once it dries, especially where the corners are. it's like things are shifting in there. should i just put another layer on top or is there something wrong with the way the wall is set up?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "*Gouging* is the key to dealing with those little gaps, and it's not just about slapping on more mud. If you see those tiny cracks, it means the underlying substrate is shifting, or you haven't properly feathered the edges. You need to use a small tool, like a putty knife or a specialized corner tool, to gently scrape out those imperfections before applying your next coat. A good, solid layer of mud is better than a thick, uneven one.",
      "source": "target",
